<h1><%= t('page.title') %></h1>
<p>This page demonstrates i18n in React Server Components using <code>React.cache()</code> and <code>react-intl/server</code>.</p>
<p>The language switcher below triggers a new RSC payload request for each locale change.</p>

<%# Demonstrate that the same YAML translations work in Rails views.
    Note: Only plain-string keys work here; ICU-format messages (plurals, select)
    are React Intl–only since Rails i18n doesn't parse ICU syntax. %>
<div style="background: #f0fdf4; padding: 12px 16px; border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid #86efac; margin: 16px 0;">
  <strong>Rails-rendered translations (from same YAML source):</strong>
  <ul style="margin: 8px 0 0 0;">
    <li><code>page.title</code>: <%= t('page.title') %></li>
    <li><code>greeting</code>: <%= t('greeting') %></li>
    <li><code>product.badge.new</code>: <%= t('product.badge.new') %></li>
  </ul>
</div>

<hr/>

<%= stream_react_component("ReactIntlRscDemoPage",
                    props: { locale: params[:locale].presence || "en" },
                    id: "ReactIntlRscDemoPage-react-component-0") %>
